trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItem"></xref> objects.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The class object provides the container for the items of an <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList>.

Accessing the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList.Items%2A> property of an <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectList> retrieves an <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItemCollection> object.
Unlike the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.MobileListItemCollection> class, an application cannot programmatically add or remove elements of this collection.
Clears the collection.
This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
This method is not available in the read-only <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.IObjectListFieldCollection> interface.
You can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.MobileListItemCollection.Clear%2A> method for all the classes where this method applies.

For example, the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.MobileListItemCollection.Clear%2A> method for a <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.StyleSheet> collection clears all the styles in the collection; or for the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.DeviceSpecificChoiceCollection>, it clears all the choices in the collection.
Adding a field to the fields of an object list changes the data-binding behavior of the control, and requires you to bind data to the control again.
Returns whether or not the given item is contained in the collection.
This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.
The item to search for.
`true` if the given item is contained in the collection; otherwise, `false`.

This API is obsolete.

An array of all the items in the <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItem"></xref> collection.

This API is obsolete.
For information about how to develop ASP.NET mobile applications, see the [www.asp.net/mobile](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=182900) Web site.

If the specified field is not found, the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItemCollection.IndexOf%2A> method returns -1.
An item to search for in the collection.
The index of the specified item in an <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItemCollection"></xref>.

The <xref href="System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListCommand"></xref> item at the specified index.

After this method has been called, the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItemCollection.IsTrackingViewState%2A> property will return `true`.

Also, the <xref:System.Web.UI.IStateManager.IsTrackingViewState%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.IStateManager> objects in the <xref:System.Web.UI.MobileControls.ObjectListItemCollection> will be set to `true`.
